# Context7

Use Context7 when implementing or debugging framework, SDK, CLI, or API-specific behavior.

- Prefer pre-resolved IDs in `.cursor/context7-libraries.md`.
- If an ID is missing, resolve it first, then update `.cursor/context7-libraries.md` when the dependency becomes part of the project.
- Keep lookups focused: ask specific questions and usually limit to about three Context7 calls per task.
- Do not send secrets, credentials, or private payloads to documentation tools.
